---
description: No TODOs, no placeholders — implement everything fully
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

Every function must be FULLY implemented.

- No `// TODO: implement this` comments
- No placeholder returns like `return null` or `return {}`
- No `// ... rest of the code` ellipsis
- No `// implement later` annotations

If a dependency file doesn't exist yet, import it anyway and note the dependency in the file header JSDoc. The file should be ready to work the moment its dependency is created.

When creating files, write the COMPLETE file content. Every function must have its full logic, error handling, and cleanup.
